Ask HN: Which college has the best undergrad CS curriculum and why?
text:
I am not limiting my question to the USA only. And world rankings are not a great measure of education at the undergrad level. It is a measure of research output and number of faculties and many other things but not education. So please don't list rankings.

A final year CS undergrad upon graduation should possess the following skills:

1. Know how to program well in multiple languages (and paradigms)

2. Knows how to solve problems and implement them in code.

3. Can build a semi large project from the ground up by making design choices.

4. Know enough mathematics to learn more later on if needed for a particular domain.

5. Communicate well.
